<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="ready-adj">ready <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'redi/    美 /'redi/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[不用于名词前] 准备好的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Come on! Aren’t you ready yet? 
快点儿！你还没准备好吗？</p></div>

<ul>
<li>be / get ready for sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Have you got ready for the exam? 
你做好考试的准备了吗？</p></div>

<ul>
<li>be / get ready to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everything is packed, and we are ready to leave. 
东西都打包好了，我们准备走了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>[只用于名词前] 迅速的；现成的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a ready answer
现成的答案</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>愿意的；乐意的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m kind, easy-going and always ready to help others.
我亲切、随和，总是乐于助人。</p><footer>2010 天津书面表达</footer></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>易于...的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t be so ready to find fault. 
不要动不动就挑毛病。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>readily  /'redɪli/ adv   </p></div>